title: FS: 1887 W.S. Kimball Champions Baseball Set Break - PSA Graded
author: premiercardcollectors

posts.post_title: FS: 1887 W.S. Kimball Champions Baseball Set Break - PSA Graded
posts.post_content:
Complete Set of all 4 Baseball Players from a relatively scarce 19th century set of athletes from the W.S. Kimball Tobacco company.  Some of the cards are stamped on the back R.M. Wade Dealer - Dry Goods, Groceries & General Merchandise - Salem, Oregon. This company is the oldest company in Oregon and still remains in business today.

Here's some great history on them:

[url]http://www.rmwade150.com/1865-1889.html[/url]

About 25 of each of these have been graded by PSA across all grades.  Beautiful and complex lithographs of the following players:

Dell Darling - 6 Seasons in the majors with 3 with the White Sox

$760

James "Tip" O'Neill - Canadian Baseball Hall of Famer and 1887 Triple Crown Winner.  Batted .326 in his 10 seasons with various teams.

$975

Hardie Henderson - Several years in the majors and led the league in wild pitches and barhouse brawls.  

$780

Ernie "E.A." Burch - One of the first true free-agents.  Was a hired gun arund the league and a solid hitter.

SOLD
